Pythonic Palette Generator 0.x Quickstart
===================================

Purpose
-------
Two small Python tools:

1) palette_gen.py
   - Extracts a wallpaper-driven palette
   - Normalizes it into Base16-style semantic slots
   - Can emit:
     - color.ini (Base16-style)
     - GTK3 00-palette.css
     - GTK2 colors.rc

2) theme_build.py
   - Imports palette_gen.py directly (same Python process, no subprocess)
   - Creates / updates the Dorakura-Kyoto theme tree
   - Generates palette files into the theme
   - Writes minimal GTK2 / GTK3 consumer files
   - Creates widget stub files if missing

------------------------------------------------------------
BASIC CONCEPT
------------------------------------------------------------

palette_gen.py = palette engine
theme_build.py = theme scaffold / assembler

Use palette_gen.py when:
- you want to inspect palette output
- you want to test extraction logic
- you want raw generated files only

Use theme_build.py when:
- you want the actual theme tree built / updated
- you want a working theme skeleton
- you want the “real” command for your personal system

------------------------------------------------------------
REQUIRED
------------------------------------------------------------

Python 3.12+
Pillow installed in your venv

Example:
    source .venv/bin/activate

------------------------------------------------------------
NORMAL PROJECT LAYOUT
------------------------------------------------------------

Recommended working dir:

    python-lab/
    ├── palette_gen.py
    └── theme_build.py

Recommended theme target:

    ~/.local/share/themes/generated-palette/

------------------------------------------------------------
PALETTE_GEN.PY QUICK USE
------------------------------------------------------------

1) Print normal Base16-style palette to stdout
----------------------------------------------

    python3 palette_gen.py /path/to/wallpaper.png

2) Print with debug info (luminance / saturation / hue)
-------------------------------------------------------

    python3 palette_gen.py /path/to/wallpaper.png --debug

3) Use the sane default surface policy
--------------------------------------

    python3 palette_gen.py /path/to/wallpaper.png --surface-style neutral --debug

4) Use stylized tinted surfaces
-------------------------------

    python3 palette_gen.py /path/to/wallpaper.png --surface-style tinted --debug

5) Write GTK3 palette file only
-------------------------------

    python3 palette_gen.py /path/to/wallpaper.png \
      --format css \
      --output ~/.local/share/themes/Dorakura-Kyoto/gtk-3.0/widgets/00-palette.css

6) Write GTK2 palette file only
-------------------------------

    python3 palette_gen.py /path/to/wallpaper.png \
      --format gtk2 \
      --output ~/.local/share/themes/Dorakura-Kyoto/gtk-2.0/colors.rc

7) Write all palette artifacts at once (recommended direct generator test)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

    python3 palette_gen.py /path/to/wallpaper.png \
      --surface-style neutral \
      --format all \
      --base16-output ~/.local/share/themes/Dorakura-Kyoto/color.ini \
      --css-output ~/.local/share/themes/Dorakura-Kyoto/gtk-3.0/widgets/00-palette.css \
      --gtk2-output ~/.local/share/themes/Dorakura-Kyoto/gtk-2.0/colors.rc

------------------------------------------------------------
PALETTE_GEN.PY IMPORTANT FLAGS
------------------------------------------------------------

--surface-style neutral
    Default / recommended
    Better structural UI surfaces
    Safer for GTK

--surface-style tinted
    More stylized / colorful dark surfaces
    Good for “art mode” or mood builds
    Not the default for sane general theming

--format base16
    Print Base16-style INI output

--format css
    Print GTK3 palette CSS (00-palette.css content)

--format gtk2
    Print GTK2 colors.rc content

--format all
    Emit all formats
    Best when paired with:
        --base16-output
        --css-output
        --gtk2-output

--debug
    Prints per-slot:
    - hex
    - luminance
    - saturation
    - hue

------------------------------------------------------------
THEME_BUILD.PY QUICK USE
------------------------------------------------------------

1) First real build (recommended)
---------------------------------

    python3 theme_build.py /path/to/wallpaper.png

This:
- creates the Dorakura-Kyoto tree if missing
- generates:
  - color.ini
  - gtk-2.0/colors.rc
  - gtk-3.0/widgets/00-palette.css
- writes:
  - index.theme
  - gtk-2.0/gtkrc
  - gtk-3.0/gtk.css
  - gtk-3.0/gtk-dark.css
- creates widget stub files only if missing

2) Use the sane default explicitly
----------------------------------

    python3 theme_build.py /path/to/wallpaper.png \
      --surface-style neutral

3) Use tinted surfaces
----------------------

    python3 theme_build.py /path/to/wallpaper.png \
      --surface-style tinted

4) Use your current test image
------------------------------

    python3 theme_build.py path_to/picture_style.png

5) Overwrite consumer entry files only
--------------------------------------

    python3 theme_build.py /path/to/wallpaper.png \
      --surface-style neutral \
      --force-consumers

This overwrites:
- index.theme
- gtk-2.0/gtkrc
- gtk-3.0/gtk.css
- gtk-3.0/gtk-dark.css

6) Overwrite widget stubs too (dangerous)
-----------------------------------------

    python3 theme_build.py /path/to/wallpaper.png \
      --surface-style neutral \
      --force-consumers \
      --force-widgets

WARNING:
This can overwrite your widget CSS module work.

------------------------------------------------------------
THEME_BUILD.PY IMPORTANT FLAGS
------------------------------------------------------------

--theme-root PATH
    Change the target theme directory

Default:
    ~/.local/share/themes/Dorakura-Kyoto

Example:
    python3 theme_build.py wallpaper.png \
      --theme-root ~/.local/share/themes/Dorakura-Kyoto

--theme-name
    Theme display name written into index.theme

Default:
    Dorakura-Kyoto

--scheme-name
    Name written into color.ini output

Default:
    Dorakura-Auto

--author
    Author string for generated palette outputs

Default:
    theme_build.py

--surface-style neutral|tinted
    Passed through to palette_gen.py logic

--force-consumers
    Overwrite consumer files

--force-widgets
    Overwrite widget stub files
    Use only if you intentionally want to regenerate them

